  user(id: &quot;{id}&quot;) {
    name
  }
}</code></pre>
  </div>
</div>

<p>Updating or deleting this user with GraphQL will not be as clear as with REST.
How will be named the mutation allowing me to delete a user? <code>deleteUser</code>, <code>removeUser</code> or <code>suppressPeople</code>?
Youâ€™ll have to dig in the documentation to find out. You cannot guess it because different API providers will have different naming conventions and these naming convention may event not be consistent within an API.</p>

<div class="card card-code text-white bg-dark border-dark">
  
  <div class="card-header">
    <div class="row m-0">
      <div class="col align-self-center">
